article.headline: Jackson State 61, Miss. Valley St. 51
article.story: ITTA BENA, Miss. (AP) -- Trey Johnson scored 20 points to lead Jackson State to a 61-51 victory over Mississippi Valley State on Saturday. Charlie White added 14 points for the Tigers (9-11), which lead 28-26 at the half. Stanford Speech led MVSU (6-11) with 15 points. Jeffery Price put 12 on the board and grabbed 10 rebounds for MVSU and Kadrian Bryant added 12 points.
